A = \begin{pmatrix}\tfrac12 & \tfrac13\\[6pt]\tfrac14 & \tfrac15\end{pmatrix}  
we first compute its determinant  
det A = (½)(⅕) − (⅓)(¼) = 1/10 − 1/12 = (6−5)/60 = 1/60.  
Hence  
A⁻¹ = (1/det A) · \begin{pmatrix}d & −b\\[3pt]−c & a\end{pmatrix}  
= 60 · \begin{pmatrix}1/5 & −1/3\\[3pt]−1/4 & 1/2\end{pmatrix}  
