First write the system in matrix form A X = B where

  A = \begin{pmatrix}4 & -5\\-1 & 2\end{pmatrix},  
  X=\begin{pmatrix}x\\y\end{pmatrix},  
  B=\begin{pmatrix}-50\\80\end{pmatrix}.  

1.  Compute det A = 4·2 − (−5)(−1) = 8 − 5 = 3.  
2.  The inverse of A is  
     A⁻¹ = (1/det A)\,\begin{pmatrix}2 & 5\\1 & 4\end{pmatrix}  
     because for \(\begin{pmatrix}a&b\\c&d\end{pmatrix}^{-1}=(1/(ad-bc))\begin{pmatrix}d&-b\\-c&a\end{pmatrix}.\)  
3.  Multiply A⁻¹ by B:  
     A⁻¹B = \frac1{3}\begin{pmatrix}2&5\\1&4\end{pmatrix}\begin{pmatrix}-50\\80\end{pmatrix}  
           = \frac1{3}\begin{pmatrix}2·(−50)+5·80\\1·(−50)+4·80\end{pmatrix}  
           = \frac1{3}\begin{pmatrix}−100+400\\−50+320\end{pmatrix}  
           = \frac1{3}\begin{pmatrix}300\\270\end{pmatrix}  
           = \begin{pmatrix}100\\90\end{pmatrix}.  

Hence x = 100, y = 90.
